anacron: An anachronistic CRON
anacron:
anacron: Anacron is a periodic command scheduler. It executes commands
anacron: at intervals specified in days. Unlike cron, it does not assume
anacron: that the system is running continuously. It can therefore be used
anacron: to control the execution of daily, weekly and monthly jobs (or
anacron: anything with a period of n days), on systems that don't run 24
anacron: hours a day. When installed and configured properly, Anacron will
anacron: make sure that the commands are run at the specified intervals
anacron: as closely as machine-uptime permits.
anacron:
